<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This module has NONE: that is the chapter's point made by the build. The value types are immutable
    records, the catalog service holds only injected ports and an in-memory map it owns, and the HTTP
    server copies request/response bytes in and out, so the representation-exposure detectors
    (EI_EXPOSE_REP / EI_EXPOSE_REP2) stay quiet without any suppression. The filter is kept (empty) so
    a future, genuinely-reviewed suppression has a home with a reason, rather than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
